Good product, in my case the motherboard read it as i7 3770 2 Core 4 Thread. I fixed it in the bios, you can find related video's on Youtube.

Working Good And if you are looking to buy it to upgrade an older pc with compatible mobo and psu go for it you wont have to worry about next 2 or 3 years to replace it also ypu can pair it with RTX 2060 Super to squeeze more fps out of any game since it doesn't bottleneck the gpu.

Awesome products. Working like a charm. But u can see some old use marks. Although that's not a big deal. But the price is a little bit high from my point of view. U can use it without any issue. But Windows 11 is not officially supported so point that.Other wise the processor can compit with i3 10100 if paired with a good gpu like rx 580.

Great performance upgrade for someone with a compatible existing h61 motherboard. Performs pretty well. The only downside is the price. For a used processor it could've been lower. I play valorant at 120 fps locked with no problems so far. NFS Heat can hardly run at 60fps in ultra. I've paired it with a 1650.
